annotation.Title: Frescoes in the Cupola
annotation.Content: "Johann Michael Rottmayr's fresco,", "painted between 1725 and 1730,", "depicts the Apotheosis of St. Charles Borromeo.", "It was the painter's last commission."

annotation.Title: The Two Columns - Left
annotation.Content: "Inspired by Trajan's Column in Rome,", "they are decorated with spiralling scenes", "of St. Charles Borromeo's life.", "Qualities of Steadfastness are illustrated", "on the left and Courage on the right."

annotation.Title: The Two Columns - Right
annotation.Content: "Inspired by Trajan's Column in Rome,", "they are decorated with spiralling scenes", "of St. Charles Borromeo's life.", "Qualities of Steadfastness are illustrated", "on the left and Courage on the right."

annotation.Title: St. Charles Borromeo
annotation.Content: "Lorenzo Mattielli's statue of the patron", "saint crowns the pediment."

annotation.Title: University of Technology
annotation.Content: "The Technical University with its", "Neo-Classical facade (1816)", "fronts on to Ressel Park, which contains", "busts and statues of famous 19th-century", "Austrian scientists and engineers."
